2️⃣ Important Concepts
🔹 GDP (Gross Domestic Product)

Total value of goods and services produced in a country in one year.

🔹 Inflation

Increase in price of goods and services over time.

🔹 RBI (Reserve Bank of India)

Central bank of India

Controls monetary policy

Issues currency

Established → 1935

🔹 Budget

Annual financial statement of government.

Presented by Finance Minister in Parliament.

🔹 Banking

Types of banks:

Commercial banks

Cooperative banks

Regional Rural Banks

